search:dotnet-efcore-postgresql-advanced.content:
- Install EF Core provider via NuGet: `dotnet add package Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL`
- Ensure PostgreSQL server is running and accessible.
- Use latest version of Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL for compatibility.
- Configure DbContext in your project:
  ```csharp
  public class MyDbContext : DbContext
  {
      public DbSet<MyEntity> MyEntities { get; set; }

      protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder optionsBuilder)
      {
          optionsBuilder.UseNpgsql("Host=myhost;Database=mydatabase;Username=myuser;Password=mypassword");
      }
  }
  ```
- Key config options in `OnConfiguring` include connection string details.
- Use LINQ to query data:
  ```csharp
  var entities = context.MyEntities.Where(e => e.SomeProperty == "value").ToList();
  ```
- For advanced features, refer to official Npgsql and EF Core documentation.
